In [[human–computer interaction]], '''MPG''' stands for "[[multi-touch]], [[physics]] and [[gestures]]",<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.google.com/buzz/mike.elgan/jEYQpNnhvX4/PCmag-com-Editor-in-Chief-Lance-Ulanoff-said-in-a|title=Multi-Touch, Physics and Gestures|author=[[Mike Elgan]]}}</ref> referencing a common method of interacting with computers and various electronic devices. The most notable MPG device is the [[Apple Inc]] [[iPhone]], which makes use of many multi-touch gestures to operate various functions of the phone and applications on the phone.
